items.sentence: I don't think that Tom has very many friends in Australia.
I didn't tell Tom that I'd never been to Australia before.
She's my oldest friend. I've known her since kindergarden.
She's made up her mind and refuses to be talked out of it.
I went over to Tom's as soon as I heard he needed my help.
If you want to know a country, you must learn its history.
Tom should've known better than to get involved with Mary.
Next time, keep your mouth shut and let me do the talking.
This is the first time I've ever put out a fire with sand.
Tom is showing Mary the new saxophone that he just bought.
